s been struggling on several fronts in recent years, including trouble in its \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;External link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://ew.com/movies/new-dc-boss-stands-by-batgirl-cancellation/\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://ew.com/movies/new-dc-boss-stands-by-batgirl-cancellation/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003etelevision and film arms\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e. Following Warner’s mishandling of so much talent and so many otherwise reliable franchises, the creatives who made great games like the \u003cem\u003eMiddle-earth \u003c/em\u003eseries have now been caught in the crossfire. One deeply frustrating wrinkle in this is that one of Monolith Productions’ greatest claims to fame has been patented by the same company that just shut down the studio. - Kenneth Shepard \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/monolith-productions-middle-earth-nemesis-system-patent-1851766437\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/monolith-productions-middle-earth-nemesis-system-patent-1851766437\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"43ccf1ba9cd6f04288fc24f775371936\" data-recommend-id=\"image://43ccf1ba9cd6f04288fc24f775371936\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"true\" data-imagerights=\"other-license\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/43ccf1ba9cd6f04288fc24f775371936.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/43ccf1ba9cd6f04288fc24f775371936.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/43ccf1ba9cd6f04288fc24f775371936.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Image for article titled Two Point Museum Is Great, The Nemesis System (RIP Monolith) Was Incredible, And More Of The Week\u0026amp;#39;s Takes\" data-chomp-id=\"43ccf1ba9cd6f04288fc24f775371936\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"1080\" data-alt=\"Image for article titled Two Point Museum Is Great, The Nemesis System (RIP Monolith) Was Incredible, And More Of The Week\u0026amp;#39;s Takes\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/43ccf1ba9cd6f04288fc24f775371936.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: FromSoftware\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"43ccf1ba9cd6f04288fc24f775371936\" data-recommend-id=\"image://43ccf1ba9cd6f04288fc24f775371936\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eWhat is a role-playing game? You probably have your own definition and exceptions. And as you might expect, nearly everyone at \u003cem\u003eKotaku \u003c/em\u003ehas thoughts and opinions on what is and isn’t an RPG. For example, some think Elden Ring is an RPG. Others disagree strongly. And then some think the idea of categorizing games via genre is a waste of time.  - Zack Zwiezen \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/is-elden-ring-rpg-action-adventure-genre-debate-kotaku-1851766667\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/is-elden-ring-rpg-action-adventure-genre-debate-kotaku-1851766667\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"18053b4b79d7d0c0bcfe058898e06093\" data-recommend-id=\"image://18053b4b79d7d0c0bcfe058898e06093\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1199\" data-height=\"675\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"Pikachu, Charizard, Gardevoir, and Lucario face off in a two-on-two battle.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"Pikachu, Charizard, Gardevoir, and Lucario face off in a two-on-two battle.\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"true\" data-imagerights=\"other-license\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/18053b4b79d7d0c0bcfe058898e06093.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/18053b4b79d7d0c0bcfe058898e06093.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/18053b4b79d7d0c0bcfe058898e06093.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Pikachu, Charizard, Gardevoir, and Lucario face off in a two-on-two battle.\" data-chomp-id=\"18053b4b79d7d0c0bcfe058898e06093\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"675\" data-alt=\"Pikachu, Charizard, Gardevoir, and Lucario face off in a two-on-two battle.\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/18053b4b79d7d0c0bcfe058898e06093.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: The Pokémon Company\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"18053b4b79d7d0c0bcfe058898e06093\" data-recommend-id=\"image://18053b4b79d7d0c0bcfe058898e06093\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1199\" data-height=\"675\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"Pikachu, Charizard, Gardevoir, and Lucario face off in a two-on-two battle.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eWe didn’t see \u003cem\u003ePokémon Champions\u003c/em\u003e in motion during the \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/pokemon-day-presents-legends-z-a-tcg-pocket-switch-1851766680?_gl=1*1d9ymxg*_ga*MTc0MjY2NTg1OS4xNzQwMzc1OTc4*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTc0MDc2NTY5Ni4xNy4xLjE3NDA3Njk1NjUuMTguMC4w\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/pokemon-day-presents-legends-z-a-tcg-pocket-switch-1851766680?_gl=1*1d9ymxg*_ga*MTc0MjY2NTg1OS4xNzQwMzc1OTc4*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTc0MDc2NTY5Ni4xNy4xLjE3NDA3Njk1NjUuMTguMC4w\"\u003ePokémon Presents showcase today\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e, but the new battle simulator might be the most important announcement made during the presentation. The game is being positioned as the future of \u003cem\u003ePokémon\u003c/em\u003e’s competitive play, as evidenced by the teaser trailer showing players using items like Game Boy link cables to battle, all culminating in a modern-day battle between a Switch user and a mobile player in \u003cem\u003eChampions\u003c/em\u003e. While the average trainer is probably most excited to return to Kalos in \u003cem\u003ePokémon Legends: Z-A\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem\u003eChampions \u003c/em\u003ecould fundamentally change how competitive \u003cem\u003ePokémon \u003c/em\u003eoperates, and by extension open up a design space for RPGs like \u003cem\u003eZ-A\u003c/em\u003e. - Kenneth Shepard \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/pokemon-champions-legends-z-a-presents-day-stream-1851766818\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/pokemon-champions-legends-z-a-presents-day-stream-1851766818\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"97b764190b392f58a1f206d3693ecad9\" data-recommend-id=\"image://97b764190b392f58a1f206d3693ecad9\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"A black and white photograph of Viktor Antonov, his hand on his chin.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"A black and white photograph of Viktor Antonov, his hand on his chin.\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"true\" data-imagerights=\"fair-use\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/97b764190b392f58a1f206d3693ecad9.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/97b764190b392f58a1f206d3693ecad9.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/97b764190b392f58a1f206d3693ecad9.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"A black and white photograph of Viktor Antonov, his hand on his chin.\" data-chomp-id=\"97b764190b392f58a1f206d3693ecad9\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"1080\" data-alt=\"A black and white photograph of Viktor Antonov, his hand on his chin.\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/97b764190b392f58a1f206d3693ecad9.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003ePhoto: Combine Overwiki / Kotaku (\u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;External link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://combineoverwiki.net/wiki/File:Viktor_Antonov.jpg\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://combineoverwiki.net/wiki/File:Viktor_Antonov.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003eFair Use\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e)\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"97b764190b392f58a1f206d3693ecad9\" data-recommend-id=\"image://97b764190b392f58a1f206d3693ecad9\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"A black and white photograph of Viktor Antonov, his hand on his chin.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eIt was announced last week that video game artist Viktor Antonov had died at the unreasonably young age of 52. With stints working at big-name studios like Valve and Arkane, Antonov’s work was a key part of some of the most loved games of all time. It was his unmistakable style that defined \u003cem\u003eHalf-Life 2\u003c/em\u003e\u0026#39;s City 17 and \u003cem\u003eDishonored\u003c/em\u003e’s Dunwall, two of the most distinctive and unforgettable locations in game history. We spoke to people who knew and loved him to learn more about Antonov and his work. - John Walker \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/viktor-antonov-half-life-2-dishonored-artist-obituary-1851765954\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/viktor-antonov-half-life-2-dishonored-artist-obituary-1851765954\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"194bb21b9b1121933768ab65bc86d19f\" data-recommend-id=\"image://194bb21b9b1121933768ab65bc86d19f\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"true\" data-imagerights=\"other-license\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/194bb21b9b1121933768ab65bc86d19f.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/194bb21b9b1121933768ab65bc86d19f.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/194bb21b9b1121933768ab65bc86d19f.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Image for article titled Two Point Museum Is Great, The Nemesis System (RIP Monolith) Was Incredible, And More Of The Week\u0026amp;#39;s Takes\" data-chomp-id=\"194bb21b9b1121933768ab65bc86d19f\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"1080\" data-alt=\"Image for article titled Two Point Museum Is Great, The Nemesis System (RIP Monolith) Was Incredible, And More Of The Week\u0026amp;#39;s Takes\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/194bb21b9b1121933768ab65bc86d19f.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: Two Point Studios / Sega\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"194bb21b9b1121933768ab65bc86d19f\" data-recommend-id=\"image://194bb21b9b1121933768ab65bc86d19f\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/games/two-point-museum\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/games/two-point-museum\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eTwo Point Museum\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cem\u003e—\u003c/em\u003eout March 4 on PC and consoles\u003cem\u003e—\u003c/em\u003eis the latest game in the \u003cem\u003eTwo Point\u003c/em\u003e series of wacky British business simulators. This time around, instead of running a hospital or building a profitable college, you are tasked with building and maintaining a successful museum. Doing so is tricky, but in a perfectly irresistible way that has sucked hours of my life away in a blink of an eye. - Zack Zwiezen \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/two-point-museum-review-pc-ps5-is-it-good-sim-tycoon-1851766450\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/two-point-museum-review-pc-ps5-is-it-good-sim-tycoon-1851766450\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"05c69ea4bf28dfc126fce03ebf432cc1\" data-recommend-id=\"image://05c69ea4bf28dfc126fce03ebf432cc1\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"A photo shows a game recommendation app. \" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"A photo shows a game recommendation app. \" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"true\" data-imagerights=\"other-license\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/05c69ea4bf28dfc126fce03ebf432cc1.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/05c69ea4bf28dfc126fce03ebf432cc1.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/05c69ea4bf28dfc126fce03ebf432cc1.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"A photo shows a game recommendation app. \" data-chomp-id=\"05c69ea4bf28dfc126fce03ebf432cc1\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"1080\" data-alt=\"A photo shows a game recommendation app. \" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/05c69ea4bf28dfc126fce03ebf432cc1.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003ePhoto: Ludocene\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"05c69ea4bf28dfc126fce03ebf432cc1\" data-recommend-id=\"image://05c69ea4bf28dfc126fce03ebf432cc1\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"A photo shows a game recommendation app. \" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003e What if finding the perfect game to play was as easy as swiping left and right in a dating app, minus the actual horrors of online dating? That’s part of the pitch behind Ludocene, an app for game recommendations that uses humans rather than machines to tell you what to play. The other part of the pitch is turning personal gaming taste into a slick-looking deckbuilder rogulite.  - Ethan Gach \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/game-recommendation-app-ludoscene-dating-deckbuilder-1851765948\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/game-recommendation-app-ludoscene-dating-deckbuilder-1851765948\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"0a4b9713f7fb2545a75ccebde8d6872a\" data-recommend-id=\"image://0a4b9713f7fb2545a75ccebde8d6872a\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1024\" data-height=\"576\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"A grim ol\u0026#39; monster in a silly hat from Command \u0026amp; Conquer: Renegade.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"A grim ol\u0026#39; monster in a silly hat from Command \u0026amp; Conquer: Renegade.\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"true\" data-imagerights=\"fair-use\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/0a4b9713f7fb2545a75ccebde8d6872a.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/0a4b9713f7fb2545a75ccebde8d6872a.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/0a4b9713f7fb2545a75ccebde8d6872a.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"A grim ol\u0026#39; monster in a silly hat from Command \u0026amp; Conquer: Renegade.\" data-chomp-id=\"0a4b9713f7fb2545a75ccebde8d6872a\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"576\" data-alt=\"A grim ol\u0026#39; monster in a silly hat from Command \u0026amp; Conquer: Renegade.\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/0a4b9713f7fb2545a75ccebde8d6872a.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eScreenshot: EA / Mobygames / Kotaku\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"0a4b9713f7fb2545a75ccebde8d6872a\" data-recommend-id=\"image://0a4b9713f7fb2545a75ccebde8d6872a\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1024\" data-height=\"576\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"A grim ol\u0026#39; monster in a silly hat from Command \u0026amp; Conquer: Renegade.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe world is built on sharing. Sure, it might seem like the most counter-cultural act imaginable amidst these late-stage capitalism end-of-days horrors, but the very internet on which you’re reading these words wouldn’t exist without it. The games you play depend on it. It’s the very core of art itself. So, it’s generally a pretty good thing when games industry people remember this. Speaking of which, EA just made the code for the first four \u003cem\u003eCommand \u0026amp; Conquer\u003c/em\u003e games officially open source. - John Walker \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/command-conquer-ea-source-code-red-alert-generals-1851767009\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/command-conquer-ea-source-code-red-alert-generals-1851767009\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"e2cf96d2267edc1d82c380a94b25ebd2\" data-recommend-id=\"image://e2cf96d2267edc1d82c380a94b25ebd2\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1998\" data-height=\"1125\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"The Shovel Knight Live concert band is shown on stage.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"The Shovel Knight Live concert band is shown on stage.\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"true\" data-imagerights=\"fair-use\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/e2cf96d2267edc1d82c380a94b25ebd2.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/e2cf96d2267edc1d82c380a94b25ebd2.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/e2cf96d2267edc1d82c380a94b25ebd2.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"The Shovel Knight Live concert band is shown on stage.\" data-chomp-id=\"e2cf96d2267edc1d82c380a94b25ebd2\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"1125\" data-alt=\"The Shovel Knight Live concert band is shown on stage.\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/e2cf96d2267edc1d82c380a94b25ebd2.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003ePhoto: Kenneth Shepard\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"e2cf96d2267edc1d82c380a94b25ebd2\" data-recommend-id=\"image://e2cf96d2267edc1d82c380a94b25ebd2\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1998\" data-height=\"1125\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"The Shovel Knight Live concert band is shown on stage.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eOn Saturday, February 22, I hiked up to the Town Hall music venue in Manhattan for Shovel Knight Live: Steel Thy Concert, in which an orchestral and rock ensemble performed tunes from Yacht Club’s hugely popular platformer. I haven’t played \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/the-seven-year-saga-of-shovel-knight-is-finally-over-1840419716\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/the-seven-year-saga-of-shovel-knight-is-finally-over-1840419716\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eShovel Knight\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cem\u003e \u003c/em\u003ein nearly a decade, but I love live music and the thought of hearing the game’s chiptune soundtrack rearranged for live instrumentation was enough to pique my interest. It wasn’t until I saw a sign stating that recording and taking photos during the performance was prohibited, however, that I realized how few \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/shovel-knight-the-kotaku-review-1595949649\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/shovel-knight-the-kotaku-review-1595949649\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eShovel Knight\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cem\u003e \u003c/em\u003efans would ever get to hear the stunning arrangements performed at the extremely limited engagement. - Kenneth Shepard \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/shovel-knight-live-steel-thy-concert-nyc-la-dates-1851766428\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/shovel-knight-live-steel-thy-concert-nyc-la-dates-1851766428\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
